other_tests.findings: Sinus tachycardia at a rate of 110 beats per minute, PR interval of 116 msec, corrected QT interval of 422 msec, and evidence of an incomplete right bundle-branch block.
Normal functioning in oral anatomy, observed diminished oral motor skills with anterior tongue position during swallowing, and signs of behavioral dysphagia.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Improvement in oral motor coordination was reported after verbal and visual instructions and practice with boluses of applesauce.
